Macaroon is a light snack, common in Europe that is prepared in less than 45 minutes. This is a small light biscuit that was made famous by the French. Texturally, the outer macaroon shell should be crunchy, while the inside should be soft and chewy. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Preheat the oven to slow (150 to 130 degrees). Grease the oven tray with butter. Step 2 In a small bowl, beat the egg yolk and sugar until creamy then add the coconut Step 3 In a different bowl, beat the egg white until it foams Step 4 Stir in the yolk-coconut mixture and stir gently Step 5 Drop the heaped teaspoon of the mixture onto the prepared trays then bake for 15 minutes. Step 6 Reduce the oven temperature to 100 or 120 degrees. Then bake for another 30 minutes or until golden brown Remove from oven and cool. Enjoy with the desired beverage or a cold glass of mango or apple juice. Dip in your favourite syrup or chocolate.